<!-- logback.xml — JSON output for EKS log aggregation -->
<configuration>
    <appender name="STDOUT" class="ch.qos.logback.core.ConsoleAppender">
        <encoder class="net.logstash.logback.encoder.LogstashEncoder">
            <includeMdcKeyName>correlationId</includeMdcKeyName>
        </encoder>
    </appender>
    <root level="INFO">
        <appender-ref ref="STDOUT" />
    </root>
</configuration>
```

Key points:

- **kotlin-logging** wraps SLF4J with lazy evaluation (`logger.info { }` — no string concat if level is off)
- **LogstashEncoder** outputs JSON — plays nicely with your EKS log pipeline
- **CorrelationIdContext** propagates the ID across coroutine dispatchers via MDC, matching what auth-service and notification-service already do
- gRPC interceptor extracts or generates the correlation ID from metadata headers

This is the same pattern as your existing production services. No new infrastructure, no new dependencies beyond what the team already uses.
